01:02:26.325 --> 01:02:28.661 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this month’s video postcard,

01:02:28.661 --> 01:02:32.632 line:90% position:50% align:center
we go to the island
of Newfoundland in Canada.

01:02:32.632 --> 01:02:37.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
A large island at the far eastern coast
of North America,

01:02:37.403 --> 01:02:41.107 line:90% position:50% align:center
Newfoundland is an amazing place of unique

01:02:41.107 --> 01:02:44.610 line:90% position:50% align:center
contrasts in weather, geography,

01:02:44.610 --> 01:02:46.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
and natural beauty.

01:02:47.113 --> 01:02:49.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sister Edith Mason brought the truth here

01:02:49.549 --> 01:02:51.851 line:90% position:50% align:center
more than a century ago.

01:02:51.851 --> 01:02:56.689 line:90% position:50% align:center
She was a single,
full-time minister in Nova Scotia.

01:02:56.689 --> 01:03:00.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1914, she resolved to go by herself

01:03:00.827 --> 01:03:05.631 line:90% position:50% align:center
to preach in Newfoundland
where there were no Witnesses at that time.

01:03:05.631 --> 01:03:08.468 line:90% position:50% align:center
After much prayer and planning,

01:03:08.468 --> 01:03:11.604 line:90% position:50% align:center
she arranged
for the “Photo-Drama of Creation”

01:03:11.604 --> 01:03:15.007 line:90% position:50% align:center
to be brought here in 1916.

01:03:15.007 --> 01:03:17.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
Over 10,000 people

01:03:17.510 --> 01:03:21.214 line:90% position:50% align:center
viewed this ground-breaking presentation.

01:03:21.214 --> 01:03:24.383 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some of the early preaching work
was done by boat.

01:03:24.383 --> 01:03:28.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
Over the years, the brothers used
four missionary boats

01:03:28.688 --> 01:03:33.493 line:90% position:50% align:center
to cover over 6,400 kilometers,

01:03:33.493 --> 01:03:37.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
or more than 4,000 miles,
of coastal territory.

01:03:38.064 --> 01:03:42.034 line:90% position:50% align:center
After the second world war,
spiritual activity increased.

01:03:42.034 --> 01:03:44.203 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1945,

01:03:44.203 --> 01:03:46.906 line:90% position:50% align:center
a branch office was established,

01:03:46.906 --> 01:03:50.543 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the first group
of Gilead-trained missionaries arrived.

01:03:50.543 --> 01:03:53.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
The branch office continued to operate

01:03:53.246 --> 01:03:55.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
until 1981.

01:03:55.615 --> 01:04:00.520 line:90% position:50% align:center
Gilead graduates Bernie and Elizabeth Mahler
were assigned to Newfoundland.

01:04:00.520 --> 01:04:02.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
They helped establish a congregation

01:04:02.755 --> 01:04:06.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
in Bonavista in 1952.

01:04:06.092 --> 01:04:09.462 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, the Bonavista Congregation has

01:04:09.462 --> 01:04:13.466 line:90% position:50% align:center
38 publishers and 4 regular pioneers.

01:04:13.466 --> 01:04:16.202 line:90% position:50% align:center
The need remains great in Newfoundland.

01:04:16.202 --> 01:04:21.207 line:90% position:50% align:center
Almost 30 percent of Canada’s
unassigned territory is here.

01:04:21.207 --> 01:04:23.809 line:90% position:50% align:center
When publishers come to help,

01:04:23.809 --> 01:04:25.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
they enjoy Newfoundland’s

01:04:25.645 --> 01:04:29.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
well-known, warm hospitality.

01:04:29.448 --> 01:04:32.685 line:90% position:50% align:center
